127
00:11:01.300 --> 00:11:03.184
It is time.

128
00:11:10.393 --> 00:11:12.893
Your pagan confidant
awaits you.

129
00:11:12.979 --> 00:11:14.979
(Petra laughs)

130
00:11:15.064 --> 00:11:17.064
As does your
fur-covered squire.

131
00:11:17.116 --> 00:11:18.232
(sheep bleats)

132
00:11:18.317 --> 00:11:19.483
I'm looking.

133
00:11:19.569 --> 00:11:20.651
Calm yourself.

134
00:11:20.736 --> 00:11:22.069
You're such an impatient ewe.

135
00:11:22.121 --> 00:11:24.705
(both laughing)

136
00:11:27.877 --> 00:11:28.909
(bleats)

137
00:11:28.961 --> 00:11:30.411
I'll sheer you raw.

138
00:11:30.463 --> 00:11:32.129
throwing that in my face.

139
00:11:32.215 --> 00:11:33.998
It was but one time.

140
00:11:34.083 --> 00:11:35.382
Very dark.

141
00:11:35.418 --> 00:11:37.585
She had familiar wool.

142
00:11:37.637 --> 00:11:38.428
(bleats)

143
00:11:38.684 --> 00:11:40.185
I am true.

144
00:11:40.286 --> 00:11:42.087
And you're one to talk.

145
00:11:42.188 --> 00:11:43.421
Yeah. I see you in the fields.

146
00:11:43.522 --> 00:11:44.756
Your tartish play.

147
00:11:44.858 --> 00:11:47.092
Catching a rub
on every buck and ram.

148
00:11:47.193 --> 00:11:49.728
Mutton troubles.
my friend?

149
00:11:49.829 --> 00:11:51.362
Good day. Wilk. Petra.

150
00:11:51.463 --> 00:11:53.030
She's a bit of crankypox.

151
00:11:53.131 --> 00:11:54.465
- (bleats)
- Eh...

152
00:11:54.566 --> 00:11:55.799
I know.

153
00:11:55.901 --> 00:11:58.069
Perhaps Miriam
needs a little rest.

154
00:11:58.170 --> 00:12:00.004
That's all she does is sleep.

155
00:12:00.105 --> 00:12:01.973
Sleep. eat and shit.

156
00:12:02.074 --> 00:12:03.274
That's because it's a sheep.

157
00:12:03.375 --> 00:12:05.776
Eh?

158
00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:09.680
Oh. wit.
(laughs)

159
00:12:09.781 --> 00:12:11.448
Yeah.

160
00:12:11.549 --> 00:12:13.617
And a beautiful one.

161
00:12:13.718 --> 00:12:14.651
Yeah. I'm sorry. honeypot.

162
00:12:14.753 --> 00:12:16.253
I know. My fault.

163
00:12:16.354 --> 00:12:17.521
(chuckles)

164
00:12:18.490 --> 00:12:19.757
(sighs)

165
00:12:19.858 --> 00:12:22.659
Love spreads like
a sweet healing balm.

166
00:12:22.761 --> 00:12:23.761
Yea.
(chuckles)

167
00:12:23.862 --> 00:12:25.763
(bleats)

168
00:12:25.864 --> 00:12:27.798
(grunting)

169
00:12:31.168 --> 00:12:33.469
How many troops
with the tax collector?

170
00:12:33.570 --> 00:12:36.139
Three knights of the
familia. five horsemen.

171
00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:37.707
All skilled.

172
00:12:37.808 --> 00:12:39.976
These hooded thieves
will meet a fierce surprise.

173
00:12:40.077 --> 00:12:41.677
(grunts)

174
00:12:41.779 --> 00:12:44.747
And if their hoods
hide the faces of rebels?

175
00:12:44.848 --> 00:12:47.350
They would ride in numbers
with their wolf.

176
00:12:47.451 --> 00:12:49.719
The Byth Encil
wouldn't just steal

177
00:12:49.820 --> 00:12:52.355
a mere piece of your bounty.
my lord.

178
00:12:52.456 --> 00:12:55.091
These attacks are an
assertion of condition.

179
00:12:55.192 --> 00:12:58.295
It's righteous peasants setting
their own rule of tribute.

180
00:13:05.402 --> 00:13:07.236
Then crush them. Milus.

181
00:13:07.337 --> 00:13:09.805
They ignite the rabble.

182
00:13:09.906 --> 00:13:11.907
If they steal
from us again.

183
00:13:12.008 --> 00:13:15.110
we'll have more aspiring outlaws
than servants to wipe my shit.

184
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:16.545
(chuckles)

185
00:13:16.646 --> 00:13:18.080
Take care. fool.

186
00:13:18.181 --> 00:13:20.782
You're not scrubbing
a floor.

187
00:13:20.883 --> 00:13:22.651
<i>Mes plus sincÃ¨res excuses.</i>
<i>mon Leige.</i>

188
00:13:35.097 --> 00:13:37.265
Brother Wilk.

189
00:13:37.366 --> 00:13:39.701
(horse neighs)

190
00:13:44.341 --> 00:13:46.442
We've heard from our friends
in Glen Darby Birch.

191
00:13:46.542 --> 00:13:48.142
Ventris comes again. Collectors.

192
00:13:48.743 --> 00:13:50.544
- Already?
CALO: - More brutal than ever.

193
00:13:50.645 --> 00:13:52.546
Doubled the tax.
doubled the guards.

194
00:13:52.647 --> 00:13:54.548
TORAN: They'll be at
our door by daybreak.

195
00:13:54.649 --> 00:13:57.051
Our journey is longer
traveling off the main trails.

196
00:13:57.152 --> 00:13:59.587
We need to ride now if we want
to catch them in darkness.

197
00:14:03.492 --> 00:14:05.360
His troops will be ready for us.

198
00:14:05.461 --> 00:14:07.294
The risk grows too great.

199
00:14:07.395 --> 00:14:10.730
They'll take what little stock
and harvest we have left.

200
00:14:10.831 --> 00:14:13.266
A winter of starvation
is the greater risk.

201
00:14:18.706 --> 00:14:20.607
We can't do this without you.

202
00:14:26.113 --> 00:14:27.179
Yea.

203
00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:29.015
Gather supplies.

204
00:14:29.116 --> 00:14:30.782
We'll need to ride
before midday.

205
00:14:30.884 --> 00:14:32.551
- I want to fight. Wilk.
- No. Ash.

206
00:14:32.652 --> 00:14:34.086
- You're of better use here.
- But I'm of proper age.

207
00:14:34.187 --> 00:14:35.687
It's a proper mind
we're in need of.

208
00:14:35.788 --> 00:14:36.855
ASH:
I'm clever.

209
00:14:36.956 --> 00:14:38.257
Please. I want to help.

210
00:14:38.358 --> 00:14:39.691
BERBER:
If we need to make haste

211
00:14:39.792 --> 00:14:41.460
off beaten paths.
no one knows the woods

212
00:14:41.561 --> 00:14:43.295
- better than our clever trapper.
ASH: - Yeah. True.

213
00:14:43.397 --> 00:14:46.964
I know every twig from
here to the sea caverns.

214
00:14:47.066 --> 00:14:49.467
- Please.
- You can ride with us.

215
00:14:49.568 --> 00:14:51.469
but you don't fight.
And the sheep stays here.

216
00:14:51.570 --> 00:14:53.671
I get a hood though. right?

217
00:14:53.772 --> 00:14:55.940
Yea. I'll make you one
out of sheepskin.

218
00:14:56.042 --> 00:14:57.775
- (men laugh)
PETRA: - You can leave Miriam

219
00:14:57.876 --> 00:14:59.744
in our pen;
she'll be safe there.

220
00:14:59.845 --> 00:15:00.176
(bleats)

221
00:15:00.880 --> 00:15:02.480
You're a cruel one.
Toran Prichard.

222
00:15:02.582 --> 00:15:05.683
He's tupping mindless beasts.
and I'm the cruel one?

223
00:15:07.485 --> 00:15:08.819
Come on.
(clicks tongue)

224
00:15:08.921 --> 00:15:10.855
Come on there. boys.

225
00:15:25.170 --> 00:15:26.370
I know that look.

226
00:15:26.471 --> 00:15:28.072
You should.

227
00:15:28.173 --> 00:15:30.074
I wear it often.

228
00:15:30.175 --> 00:15:33.410
Ventris is sly and brutal.

229
00:15:33.511 --> 00:15:36.080
It's only time and chance
before you feel his blade.

230
00:15:36.181 --> 00:15:39.316
You're not a
rebel. Wilkin.

231
00:15:39.417 --> 00:15:41.318
Let the band of Byth Encil

232
00:15:41.419 --> 00:15:43.319
take their defiant
vengeance to our baron.

233
00:15:43.420 --> 00:15:46.089
This isn't about vengeance.

234
00:15:46.190 --> 00:15:47.523
You heard your father.

235
00:15:47.624 --> 00:15:50.193
We take this risk

236
00:15:50.294 --> 00:15:51.894
to survive.

237
00:15:51.995 --> 00:15:54.730
The baron's tax leech
comes twice a season now.

238
00:15:54.831 --> 00:15:56.432
We've barely stock
and food to live.

239
00:15:56.533 --> 00:16:00.603
You're the only stock
I can't live without!

240
00:16:03.606 --> 00:16:05.440
(sighs)

241
00:16:07.443 --> 00:16:09.444
ANNORA:
Good morning. farmer.

242
00:16:14.317 --> 00:16:16.918
Fair dame.

243
00:16:17.019 --> 00:16:19.454
And how is our gentle
lytling doing today?

244
00:16:19.555 --> 00:16:21.423
Very active.

245
00:16:21.524 --> 00:16:22.689
Hmm.

246
00:16:22.790 --> 00:16:24.925
A life eager

247
00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:27.694
to begin a greater journey.

248
00:16:30.132 --> 00:16:31.098
Yea.

249
00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:33.834
You must cover
this wound.

250
00:16:33.935 --> 00:16:37.605
The spill layer of the river
swims with sickness.

251
00:16:37.705 --> 00:16:39.673
I'm fine.

252
00:16:39.774 --> 00:16:41.807
And in
three days' time.

253
00:16:41.908 --> 00:16:43.709
you will be weak
and fevered.

254
00:16:45.712 --> 00:16:47.647
Boil these.

255
00:16:47.748 --> 00:16:50.183
Soak the wound
in the broth.

256
00:16:50.284 --> 00:16:51.684
Yea.

257
00:16:54.321 --> 00:16:56.356
Thank you.

258
00:17:12.738 --> 00:17:14.739
The other man.

259
00:17:20.812 --> 00:17:23.981
God has put him
on our path.

260
00:17:29.454 --> 00:17:30.954
(door opens)

261
00:17:32.957 --> 00:17:36.126
Quarter rips for
the other two quaints.

262
00:17:36.228 --> 00:17:37.595
(sighs) _

263
00:17:37.696 --> 00:17:39.063
It's double shillings
for that.

264
00:17:39.164 --> 00:17:41.899
Finish the task.

265
00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:43.767
Fair rate will follow.

266
00:17:44.803 --> 00:17:47.370
(screaming)

267
00:17:56.781 --> 00:17:58.348
(sighs)

268
00:17:58.449 --> 00:18:00.117
Did you soak the rag
in dumb paste?

269
00:18:00.218 --> 00:18:02.518
I... I...

270
00:18:02.619 --> 00:18:04.553
The pot wouldn't fit
in the bags. Father.

271
00:18:04.654 --> 00:18:06.388
But I can...

272
00:18:13.597 --> 00:18:16.365
(panting)

273
00:18:16.466 --> 00:18:18.400
Stupid and weak.

274
00:18:22.873 --> 00:18:24.874
Stupid and weak.

275
00:18:52.347 --> 00:18:55.216
God. I hate when she does that.

276
00:19:00.523 --> 00:19:02.490
Milady?

277
00:19:02.591 --> 00:19:04.058
Lady Love?

278
00:19:06.094 --> 00:19:07.295
Shit.

279
00:19:11.733 --> 00:19:14.435
(gasps)

280
00:19:16.405 --> 00:19:17.604
(coughs)

281
00:19:21.409 --> 00:19:23.977
(sighs softly)

282
00:19:24.078 --> 00:19:26.880
Can you please
not do that. Love?

283
00:19:26.981 --> 00:19:29.650
My heart drowns
with you every time.

284
00:19:29.751 --> 00:19:32.819
I'm fine.
dear Isabel.

285
00:19:32.920 --> 00:19:35.989
I've been swimming in this
water since I was born.

286
00:19:36.090 --> 00:19:37.891
The chill refreshes
my spirit.

287
00:19:37.992 --> 00:19:39.692
Reminds me of
who I am.

288
00:19:39.794 --> 00:19:42.528
The baroness
who caught her death?

289
00:19:42.630 --> 00:19:46.867
The hopeful Welsh girl who
knows God holds her close.

290
00:19:46.968 --> 00:19:48.701
He has a journey in mind.

291
00:19:48.803 --> 00:19:50.036
Yes.

292
00:19:50.138 --> 00:19:52.305
I know that girl.

293
00:19:58.512 --> 00:20:00.713
Time is a most
aggressive foe. Milus.

294
00:20:00.814 --> 00:20:03.750
Favor of my rule
changes with the wind.

295
00:20:03.850 --> 00:20:06.419
The unrest that grows
on this damp rock...

296
00:20:06.520 --> 00:20:09.289
I need to make my gains
now. while I still hold

297
00:20:09.390 --> 00:20:11.790
the king's trust.

298
00:20:11.891 --> 00:20:13.858
Wealth. my lord.

299
00:20:13.959 --> 00:20:16.595
is the foundation
of any temple of power.

300
00:20:16.696 --> 00:20:18.963
We need to fortify
our resources.

301
00:20:19.064 --> 00:20:21.767
Steeper taxes and tariffs.

302
00:20:21.867 --> 00:20:23.168
Yes. agreed.

303
00:20:23.269 --> 00:20:26.037
Pardon. Lord Ventris.
good Chamberlain.

304
00:20:26.138 --> 00:20:28.540
Baron Pryce's emissary
waits for you at the market.

305
00:20:28.641 --> 00:20:30.442
He is... quite eager.

306
00:20:30.543 --> 00:20:33.644
I assume Pryce
sends no gifts

307
00:20:33.745 --> 00:20:35.280
with his eager
messenger?

308
00:20:35.380 --> 00:20:37.515
Gifts. Baron?

309
00:20:37.616 --> 00:20:39.784
Stuffed pheasant.
Aged wine.

310
00:20:39.885 --> 00:20:41.019
A bevy of
virgin whores.

311
00:20:41.120 --> 00:20:42.386
Why would he send such?

312
00:20:42.487 --> 00:20:44.322
Ballok cod.

313
00:20:44.423 --> 00:20:45.756
Why does he want an audience?

314
00:20:45.858 --> 00:20:46.858
Oh. yes.

315
00:20:46.959 --> 00:20:48.492
Again. he makes a heated point

316
00:20:48.593 --> 00:20:49.727
of the steep tariff.

317
00:20:49.829 --> 00:20:51.162
Asserts that Baron Pryce

318
00:20:51.263 --> 00:20:53.497
will refuse payment
if it grows again.

319
00:20:53.598 --> 00:20:55.599
If Pryce wants access to
the sea. he will pay for it.

320
00:20:55.701 --> 00:20:58.902
And if he refuses. then we
have cause to assert power.

321
00:20:59.003 --> 00:21:00.705
Into Pryceshire?

322
00:21:00.806 --> 00:21:03.607
But his legions outnumber ours.

323
00:21:03.709 --> 00:21:06.544
Pryce is a man
of books.

324
00:21:06.645 --> 00:21:09.112
Thinkers die
in battle.

325
00:21:09.214 --> 00:21:11.681
Good Baron.

326
00:21:11.782 --> 00:21:13.483
Chamberlain.

327
00:21:15.953 --> 00:21:18.355
What is our passage
for today. Father?

328
00:21:18.456 --> 00:21:21.257
Genesis.

329
00:21:21.359 --> 00:21:24.927
We're learning how
God created us in his likeness.

330
00:21:25.028 --> 00:21:27.129
Gave us a perfect world.

331
00:21:29.533 --> 00:21:32.301
Care to join us. Baron?

332
00:21:33.870 --> 00:21:36.505
Yes.

333
00:21:37.540 --> 00:21:39.608
Another time. Father.

334
00:21:49.218 --> 00:21:50.686
And what of our king?

335
00:21:50.787 --> 00:21:53.188
Where will Edward sit
in this dispute with you

336
00:21:53.289 --> 00:21:54.555
and Baron Pryce?

337
00:21:54.656 --> 00:21:56.724
Where his soft French
bottom always sits--

338
00:21:56.825 --> 00:21:58.326
in the middle.

339
00:21:58.427 --> 00:22:01.462
waiting like a flowered
girl to coo the victor.

340
00:22:01.563 --> 00:22:04.199
With a mouth
full of noble seed.

341
00:22:06.335 --> 00:22:08.536
Ah. yes.
Because he's a bit fancy.

342
00:22:08.637 --> 00:22:10.205
(door creaks)

343
00:22:14.276 --> 00:22:16.277
(cattle moos)

344
00:22:18.579 --> 00:22:20.580
(sheep bleats. horses neigh)

345
00:22:25.220 --> 00:22:27.221
(chickens clucking)

346
00:22:30.158 --> 00:22:32.458
VENTRIS:
Tell Pryce's man

347
00:22:32.559 --> 00:22:34.460
the tariff
just went up again.

348
00:22:34.561 --> 00:22:35.861
A third?

349
00:22:35.963 --> 00:22:38.264
More than fair.

350
00:22:38.365 --> 00:22:41.067
But. my lord. you...
you realize you taunt him

351
00:22:41.168 --> 00:22:42.302
by raising it
yet again?

352
00:22:42.403 --> 00:22:44.037
The taunt <i>is</i> the message.

353
00:22:44.138 --> 00:22:46.772
Deliver it.

354
00:22:46.873 --> 00:22:48.908
Yes. Sorry.

355
00:22:49.009 --> 00:22:51.010
Baron. Chamberlain.

356
00:22:53.513 --> 00:22:55.080
Hello. sir.

357
00:22:55.181 --> 00:22:56.749
VENTRIS: Your young brother
doubts our methods.

358
00:22:56.850 --> 00:22:59.084
Half my blood.

359
00:22:59.185 --> 00:23:01.019
Quarter the brains.

360
00:23:01.120 --> 00:23:02.688
(chuckles)

361
00:23:11.797 --> 00:23:13.431
ARON:
Hey.

362
00:23:13.532 --> 00:23:15.700
Give it here.
You carried Da's ax last ride.

363
00:23:15.801 --> 00:23:17.702
Yeah. because you don't have
the arm to swing it. puny-kin.

364
00:23:17.803 --> 00:23:19.036
Says you. you fat elf.

365
00:23:19.137 --> 00:23:20.872
(scoffs)

366
00:23:22.741 --> 00:23:24.408
Oh. hey. hey.
whoa. whoa. whoa. hey!

367
00:23:26.145 --> 00:23:28.880
Will you two
ever grow up?

368
00:23:32.283 --> 00:23:35.352
You should be whittling me toys.
not playing hero. old man.

369
00:23:35.453 --> 00:23:40.256
Whittling is for the lame
of mind. motherly daughter.

370
00:23:40.358 --> 00:23:42.092
(chuckles)

371
00:23:42.193 --> 00:23:44.127
Be certain that's not
how you return.

372
00:23:50.534 --> 00:23:52.568
TORAN: No need to wear
the funeral mask.

373
00:23:52.669 --> 00:23:54.003
I'm not dead yet. wife.

374
00:23:54.104 --> 00:23:55.404
The mask is for me.

375
00:23:55.506 --> 00:23:58.407
You'll be the death of me.
you reckless poke.

376
00:23:58.509 --> 00:24:00.510
Hey.

377
00:24:00.611 --> 00:24:02.244
(grunts)

378
00:24:02.345 --> 00:24:03.913
You keep her heavy on the
mead while I'm away. boy.

379
00:24:04.014 --> 00:24:04.914
She's bearable that way.

380
00:24:05.015 --> 00:24:07.449
Am I a ghost without ears?

381
00:24:07.551 --> 00:24:09.450
I will. Da.
Heaps of it.

382
00:24:09.552 --> 00:24:10.451
(chuckles)

383
00:24:10.553 --> 00:24:12.320
(grunts)

384
00:24:34.976 --> 00:24:36.944
We'll be back
before half moon.

385
00:24:37.045 --> 00:24:38.345
Yea.

386
00:24:38.446 --> 00:24:41.015
I'll be here. Twice the cow.

387
00:24:44.085 --> 00:24:45.686
You stay in there.

388
00:24:45.787 --> 00:24:47.687
No catching your mother
with a sneakish birth.

389
00:24:47.788 --> 00:24:49.321
Running the laws
of nature now. farmer?

390
00:24:49.423 --> 00:24:50.957
WILKIN:
Never. dear Eva.

391
00:24:51.058 --> 00:24:53.927
I leave the control of
all things earthly to the women.

392
00:24:59.166 --> 00:25:00.800
God keep you safe.

393
00:25:00.901 --> 00:25:01.968
Always.

394
00:25:02.069 --> 00:25:03.570
Hup.

395
00:25:03.671 --> 00:25:04.604
Hup!

396
00:25:26.500 --> 00:25:32.179
_

397
00:25:39.451 --> 00:25:42.186
(arrows whooshing)

398
00:25:55.867 --> 00:25:56.600
(grunts)

399
00:26:03.041 --> 00:26:04.041
(grunting)

400
00:26:07.578 --> 00:26:08.911
(neck snaps)

401
00:26:19.222 --> 00:26:20.957
- We meet again. tax man!
- (screams)

402
00:26:24.928 --> 00:26:28.097
(sobbing):
Oh. please. Oh. please.

403
00:26:28.198 --> 00:26:29.665
Spare me still.

404
00:26:31.234 --> 00:26:33.302
(gasping)

405
00:26:33.403 --> 00:26:34.536
Tell your greedy lord.

406
00:26:34.637 --> 00:26:37.406
if he keeps biting
like the boar.

407
00:26:37.507 --> 00:26:38.974
we keep laying the traps.

408
00:26:39.076 --> 00:26:40.375
(shouts)

409
00:26:40.476 --> 00:26:41.744
Where's your horse.
tax man?!

410
00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:52.221
(laughter)

411
00:26:57.126 --> 00:26:59.861
(men chattering. snickering)

412
00:26:59.962 --> 00:27:02.397
Here.

413
00:27:02.498 --> 00:27:06.367
Yeah. it is true. friend.

414
00:27:06.468 --> 00:27:09.403
I'll own skill of this one day.

415
00:27:09.504 --> 00:27:12.406
I'll make my little wings
that vanish on the bark.

416
00:27:12.507 --> 00:27:14.074
I will fly.

417
00:27:15.777 --> 00:27:17.211
Woden has promised me.

418
00:27:17.312 --> 00:27:19.146
(horses approaching)

419
00:27:19.248 --> 00:27:21.815
Ah. my friends return.

420
00:27:23.619 --> 00:27:25.018
(horse neighs)

421
00:27:30.458 --> 00:27:31.858
Yah!

422
00:27:41.002 --> 00:27:43.003
Bag the chattel and furs.

423
00:27:50.678 --> 00:27:52.479
♪

424
00:27:52.580 --> 00:27:54.514
(squawking)

425
00:27:54.515 --> 00:27:57.480
_

426
00:27:58.452 --> 00:28:00.919
(wings flapping)

427
00:28:05.292 --> 00:28:07.593
(horse neighs in distance)

428
00:28:07.694 --> 00:28:11.964
CORBETT: Destiny has met
your ambitious young warrior.

429
00:28:12.065 --> 00:28:15.801
Wilkin Brattle will no longer
draw favor from the king.

430
00:28:15.902 --> 00:28:18.436
The long blades
of the Scots served us well.

431
00:28:18.538 --> 00:28:21.473
An inspired plan.
good Marshal.

432
00:28:24.944 --> 00:28:26.879
Send troops
for the bodies.

433
00:28:26.980 --> 00:28:30.949
If we bring him back. Constable.

434
00:28:31.050 --> 00:28:32.951
Brattle will be seen
as a slain hero

435
00:28:33.052 --> 00:28:34.986
who stood up
to an army of Scots.

436
00:28:37.990 --> 00:28:39.991
They will immortalize him.

437
00:28:42.027 --> 00:28:43.828
Perhaps we take comfort

438
00:28:43.929 --> 00:28:47.264
knowing that we serve
God's hungry creatures.

439
00:28:47.365 --> 00:28:49.099
Yes.

440
00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:50.701
Feast on. my friends!

441
00:28:50.802 --> 00:28:52.537
King-fed meat!

442
00:28:52.638 --> 00:28:54.572
(both laugh)

443
00:29:04.782 --> 00:29:06.783
♪

444
00:29:32.309 --> 00:29:34.310
Forgive me.

445
00:29:39.275 --> 00:29:44.290
_

446
00:29:44.292 --> 00:29:46.293
DYER:
Baron Pryce.

447
00:29:47.463 --> 00:29:48.863
Pardon. my lord.

448
00:29:48.964 --> 00:29:50.632
Your emissary has returned
from Ventrishire.

449
00:29:53.102 --> 00:29:54.902
Finish with disbursement.
Chamberlain.

450
00:29:55.003 --> 00:29:56.304
Of course.

451
00:29:56.405 --> 00:29:58.272
TRULA:
Edwin.

452
00:29:58.373 --> 00:30:00.407
It is much too damp
in this room.

453
00:30:00.508 --> 00:30:01.408
Yes. my love.

454
00:30:01.509 --> 00:30:02.910
(coughs)

455
00:30:03.011 --> 00:30:05.346
Take the baroness
to the sun room.

456
00:30:08.683 --> 00:30:10.684
(coughing)

457
00:30:19.194 --> 00:30:20.594
Who's next?

458
00:30:20.695 --> 00:30:22.563
Gawain Maddox!

459
00:30:26.067 --> 00:30:28.001
The traveling punisher.

460
00:30:28.102 --> 00:30:29.470
Ah.

461
00:30:39.347 --> 00:30:40.747
(coins clink)

462
00:30:46.754 --> 00:30:49.555
You claimed fairness.

463
00:30:49.657 --> 00:30:50.991
This is half my wage.

464
00:30:51.092 --> 00:30:52.725
DYER: Do you know
how many journeymen

465
00:30:52.827 --> 00:30:55.728
pass through this shire
every week. hmm?

466
00:30:55.830 --> 00:30:59.866
Blacksmiths. bowmen. even
executioners such as yourself.

467
00:31:01.903 --> 00:31:04.905
Many flee the South
in search of work.

468
00:31:05.006 --> 00:31:07.340
That doesn't mean we don't
deserve our rightful pay.

469
00:31:07.441 --> 00:31:12.144
If you do not find this
satisfactory. move on.

470
00:31:12.245 --> 00:31:14.314
Find yourself another
shire where you can

471
00:31:14.415 --> 00:31:16.582
peddle your brutal gifts.

472
00:31:17.951 --> 00:31:19.319
Next.

473
00:31:19.420 --> 00:31:20.320
REEVE:
Barclay the minstrel.

474
00:31:20.421 --> 00:31:23.289
Ah. the minstrel.

475
00:31:27.828 --> 00:31:29.729
We travel.

476
00:31:29.830 --> 00:31:31.797
But where to. Maddy?

477
00:31:31.897 --> 00:31:33.965
To the sea.

478
00:31:34.066 --> 00:31:35.734
Ventrishire.

479
00:31:35.835 --> 00:31:37.168
Now!

480
00:31:42.842 --> 00:31:45.143
(door opens)

481
00:31:45.244 --> 00:31:47.479
CORBETT:
Forgive us. Baron.

482
00:31:47.580 --> 00:31:48.680
My lady.

483
00:31:48.781 --> 00:31:50.515
There's been
another attack.

484
00:31:50.616 --> 00:31:51.783
Hooded thieves.

485
00:31:51.884 --> 00:31:53.251
All eight of
our men slain.

486
00:31:55.221 --> 00:31:56.554
JONAS:
Took us in darkness.

487
00:31:56.655 --> 00:31:57.655
Deadly ghosts.

488
00:31:57.756 --> 00:31:59.390
- The same ones?
- Yes.

489
00:31:59.491 --> 00:32:01.392
Six. in familiar hoods.

490
00:32:01.493 --> 00:32:03.728
There was another this time.
deeper in the woods.

491
00:32:03.829 --> 00:32:05.330
Saw a flash of his face.

492
00:32:05.430 --> 00:32:06.364
A young one.

493
00:32:06.465 --> 00:32:07.665
How do you know he was a bandit?

494
00:32:07.766 --> 00:32:09.033
JONAS:
He was hooded.

495
00:32:09.134 --> 00:32:10.501
His clothing was different.

496
00:32:10.602 --> 00:32:14.071
all hides and furs.
but he was with them.

497
00:32:14.172 --> 00:32:15.373
Uh. a watcher perhaps.

498
00:32:15.474 --> 00:32:16.874
What kind of fur did he wear?

499
00:32:16.975 --> 00:32:19.610
It had sheen--
uh. beaver pelt. I'd say.

500
00:32:21.045 --> 00:32:24.548
Costly vesture
for a peasant bandit.

501
00:32:24.649 --> 00:32:27.785
Beavers.

502
00:32:27.886 --> 00:32:30.220
What rivers do they dam?

503
00:32:30.321 --> 00:32:31.221
I'm not sure.

504
00:32:31.322 --> 00:32:33.791
Colder ones. perhaps.

505
00:32:33.892 --> 00:32:35.893
West to the sea.

506
00:32:37.395 --> 00:32:40.364
West.

507
00:32:40.464 --> 00:32:42.199
Gwynedd and the minor turns.

508
00:32:42.300 --> 00:32:43.433
Here.

509
00:32:43.534 --> 00:32:45.869
Branches of the Dunoding
run west.

510
00:32:45.970 --> 00:32:47.704
Touch the far end
of the shire.

511
00:32:47.805 --> 00:32:49.706
We've settlers there?

512
00:32:49.807 --> 00:32:51.275
No. I think...

513
00:32:51.376 --> 00:32:52.309
JONAS:
Yes.

514
00:32:52.410 --> 00:32:54.111
Yes. we do.

515
00:32:54.212 --> 00:32:55.845
Barley farmers.

516
00:32:55.947 --> 00:32:57.781
West River Riding.

517
00:32:57.882 --> 00:32:59.783
Quarterly collections.

518
00:32:59.884 --> 00:33:01.617
Oh. West River.

519
00:33:01.718 --> 00:33:03.019
Yes. of course.

520
00:33:03.120 --> 00:33:04.453
Half legion and
horsemen. my charge.

521
00:33:04.554 --> 00:33:05.754
You ride with us.

522
00:33:05.855 --> 00:33:07.189
Pick out the watcher.

523
00:33:07.291 --> 00:33:08.257
Make sound guesses
of the others

524
00:33:08.358 --> 00:33:10.826
without their clever hoods.

525
00:33:10.928 --> 00:33:12.861
CORBETT:
You as well. Reeve.

526
00:33:12.963 --> 00:33:15.031
Get to know your shire.

527
00:33:15.132 --> 00:33:16.265
RANDULF:
Yes. dear brother.

528
00:33:16.366 --> 00:33:18.301
Baron. My lady.

529
00:33:23.808 --> 00:33:26.241
And what of manor law?

530
00:33:26.342 --> 00:33:29.277
Is there a mind for fairness
in your swift purpose?

531
00:33:30.613 --> 00:33:32.347
Of course. my love.

532
00:33:32.448 --> 00:33:34.382
Fair process for every man.

533
00:33:41.958 --> 00:33:44.192
I know your distress
is undoubtedly

534
00:33:44.293 --> 00:33:48.196
about the safety
of your husband. my lady.

535
00:33:48.297 --> 00:33:50.397
but an ignorant eye
may see it

536
00:33:50.499 --> 00:33:53.267
as concern
for the welfare of outlaws.

537
00:33:53.368 --> 00:33:55.703
Well. I thank my maker
that I'm in the presence

538
00:33:55.804 --> 00:33:58.739
of a man who never leans
towards ignorance.

539
00:34:00.809 --> 00:34:02.810
Indeed.

540
00:34:02.911 --> 00:34:04.612
Knowledge is my service.

541
00:34:04.713 --> 00:34:07.081
Indeed.

542
00:34:07.182 --> 00:34:11.051
Perhaps you should share some of
that knowledge with my husband.

543
00:34:11.152 --> 00:34:13.487
Let him know that his thirst
to grow this shire

544
00:34:13.588 --> 00:34:15.322
should not be quenched

545
00:34:15.423 --> 00:34:18.425
with the sweat and blood
of its own people.

546
00:34:18.526 --> 00:34:22.396
It is the people's duty
to tithe.

547
00:34:22.497 --> 00:34:24.064
Only rebels

548
00:34:24.165 --> 00:34:26.066
refuse to honor
the rule of law.

549
00:34:26.167 --> 00:34:27.801
No commoner wants rebellion.

550
00:34:27.902 --> 00:34:31.271
It only comes after hope and
reason are burned to the ground.

551
00:34:31.373 --> 00:34:33.874
Tell me. Baroness.

552
00:34:33.975 --> 00:34:36.876
How is it that someone
of your privilege

553
00:34:36.977 --> 00:34:40.246
may come to know
the plight of the common man?

554
00:34:42.316 --> 00:34:45.518
Well. unlike some
within these walls.

555
00:34:45.619 --> 00:34:48.654
I live with open eyes
and open heart.

556
00:34:51.392 --> 00:34:53.993
You will break them. Milus.

557
00:34:54.094 --> 00:34:55.895
And we both know
there's nothing more dangerous

558
00:34:55.996 --> 00:34:59.332
than a Welshman
who has nothing to lose.

559
00:35:07.841 --> 00:35:11.543
Keep my husband to a safe path.

560
00:35:11.644 --> 00:35:15.380
I'm depending on you.
good Chamberlain.

561
00:35:29.928 --> 00:35:33.130
(excited chatter and laughter
in distance)

562
00:35:36.559 --> 00:35:40.737
_

563
00:35:43.942 --> 00:35:45.442
(excited chatter continues)

564
00:35:47.845 --> 00:35:49.580
(cheering)

565
00:35:49.681 --> 00:35:52.616
MAN: Melt it down. and you
shall have whatever you like.

566
00:35:56.788 --> 00:35:58.789
(pipe playing)

567
00:36:00.992 --> 00:36:03.627
Our brave hunters approach.

568
00:36:03.728 --> 00:36:04.694
ASH:
Midshire hares!

569
00:36:04.795 --> 00:36:07.197
Big enough to mount.
(laughs)

570
00:36:07.298 --> 00:36:08.664
We want to skewer them
with sticks.

571
00:36:08.765 --> 00:36:10.166
not with our pricks.
you beast-lover.

572
00:36:10.267 --> 00:36:12.135
(laughter)

573
00:36:12.236 --> 00:36:14.137
JACOB:
Don't listen to him. boy.

574
00:36:14.238 --> 00:36:17.207
We take our comfort
wherever we find it.

575
00:36:17.308 --> 00:36:19.242
And what if you find him
taking comfort in your pen...

576
00:36:20.444 --> 00:36:21.844
...poking your prize hog?

577
00:36:21.945 --> 00:36:23.346
(laughter)

578
00:36:23.447 --> 00:36:25.180
I don't fancy hogs.

579
00:36:25.281 --> 00:36:26.582
(laughter)

580
00:36:26.683 --> 00:36:28.584
That's true.
He's a one-sheep man.

581
00:36:28.685 --> 00:36:30.686
(laughter continues)

582
00:36:39.563 --> 00:36:41.597
Why does Wilk
use oak and not a blade?

583
00:36:44.835 --> 00:36:47.002
There are many things

584
00:36:47.103 --> 00:36:49.838
we do not know about our leader.

585
00:36:49.940 --> 00:36:50.940
Even Petra knows
little of his life

586
00:36:51.041 --> 00:36:52.041
before he came to the river.

587
00:36:52.142 --> 00:36:54.209
ASH:
Had to be a soldier.

588
00:36:54.311 --> 00:36:56.778
The fight skill
he's given you--

589
00:36:56.879 --> 00:36:59.381
that was learned on a field
of battle. not barley.

590
00:36:59.482 --> 00:37:02.451
We've all tales
best kept locked in our head.

591
00:37:06.889 --> 00:37:08.490
More of your song.

592
00:37:12.762 --> 00:37:17.231
♪ ye talisman give potion... ♪

593
00:37:17.333 --> 00:37:19.300
You should eat.

594
00:37:19.401 --> 00:37:21.302
Yea.

595
00:37:21.403 --> 00:37:23.271
(singing continues in distance)

596
00:37:26.509 --> 00:37:28.743
Ventris will keep
doubling his guards.

597
00:37:28.845 --> 00:37:30.679
Yeah. we can't
do this alone anymore.

598
00:37:32.882 --> 00:37:34.516
You saw the daffodil hides
in the trees.

599
00:37:34.617 --> 00:37:36.485
The Byth Encil rebels
would welcome our skill.

600
00:37:36.586 --> 00:37:38.519
I can arrange for a meet.
and we can...

601
00:37:38.620 --> 00:37:43.123
I serve God and family.
not cause or crown.

602
00:37:43.225 --> 00:37:45.125
Give straight.
brother.

603
00:37:45.227 --> 00:37:47.395
You think the gates of
heaven will fly open

604
00:37:47.496 --> 00:37:49.730
because you down a man
with wood instead of steel?

605
00:37:49.831 --> 00:37:50.864
Perhaps not.

606
00:37:50.965 --> 00:37:53.201
We've both watched men die

607
00:37:53.302 --> 00:37:56.036
by the work of our hands.
Wilkin.

608
00:37:56.137 --> 00:38:00.441
In service of gods or king.
it doesn't matter.

609
00:38:00.542 --> 00:38:02.610
We're driven by
a deeper burn.

610
00:38:02.711 --> 00:38:06.314
and we need to feel that
or we wither.

611
00:38:32.540 --> 00:38:34.541
(horses approaching)

612
00:38:43.650 --> 00:38:45.651
Where's your man?!

613
00:38:45.753 --> 00:38:47.353
Where's your right?

614
00:38:50.490 --> 00:38:52.458
(panting)

615
00:38:59.833 --> 00:39:01.234
No farmer here.

616
00:39:01.334 --> 00:39:02.368
Only women

617
00:39:02.469 --> 00:39:04.070
and useless elders.

618
00:39:04.171 --> 00:39:06.404
Where are your men?!

619
00:39:12.111 --> 00:39:13.544
PETRA:
They're hunting.

620
00:39:13.646 --> 00:39:15.046
Lord Ventris.

621
00:39:15.148 --> 00:39:17.448
Skins for the
next harvest.

622
00:39:19.786 --> 00:39:21.719
In the dark?

623
00:39:21.821 --> 00:39:24.089
Do I seem a fool?

624
00:39:29.728 --> 00:39:31.562
Slit the boy's throat.

625
00:39:31.664 --> 00:39:34.098
No! No! No!

626
00:39:34.199 --> 00:39:35.700
Stop! Stop!

627
00:39:35.801 --> 00:39:38.102
Where are they?

628
00:39:38.203 --> 00:39:40.471
A lie bleeds two throats.

629
00:39:41.740 --> 00:39:43.874
They...

630
00:39:43.975 --> 00:39:46.043
they went to Glen Darby Birch.

631
00:39:46.144 --> 00:39:48.245
With their hoods?

632
00:39:52.284 --> 00:39:53.718
(screams)

633
00:39:53.819 --> 00:39:55.452
Yea! With hoods!

634
00:39:55.553 --> 00:39:56.887
How many?

635
00:39:56.988 --> 00:39:57.988
Seven.

636
00:39:58.089 --> 00:39:59.656
You expect your baron
to believe

637
00:39:59.757 --> 00:40:01.926
that a pox-dowed band of farmers

638
00:40:02.027 --> 00:40:04.594
have skill enough
to knell our noble ranks?

639
00:40:04.696 --> 00:40:05.930
He should.

640
00:40:06.031 --> 00:40:07.531
His ranks

641
00:40:07.632 --> 00:40:10.234
seem only fit to strike
women and children!

642
00:40:14.706 --> 00:40:15.840
(Eva screaming)

643
00:40:15.941 --> 00:40:17.041
(sobbing)

644
00:40:19.743 --> 00:40:21.244
(screaming)

645
00:40:27.918 --> 00:40:29.385
Kill them all.

646
00:40:31.388 --> 00:40:32.856
Burn it to the ground.

647
00:40:32.957 --> 00:40:34.790
PETRA:
You devils!

648
00:40:34.892 --> 00:40:36.826
You curs!

649
00:40:36.927 --> 00:40:41.264
They will hunt you down
and cut out your stone hearts!

650
00:40:41.365 --> 00:40:44.733
Make this one a sight
for deep memory.

651
00:40:44.834 --> 00:40:46.434
Brutal.

652
00:40:46.535 --> 00:40:48.737
Let it strike a pain
that cannot be hidden

653
00:40:48.838 --> 00:40:50.772
with insolent hoods.

654
00:40:50.874 --> 00:40:52.707
(screaming)
Run. Petra!

655
00:40:54.310 --> 00:40:56.245
(laughs)
Fetch her!

656
00:40:57.380 --> 00:40:59.982
(Eva screaming)

657
00:41:06.621 --> 00:41:08.589
This is a breach of law.

658
00:41:08.690 --> 00:41:10.391
Both God and king.

659
00:41:10.492 --> 00:41:11.525
It-it...

660
00:41:11.626 --> 00:41:14.795
This is madness!

661
00:41:14.897 --> 00:41:17.731
Please. my lord.
Please.

662
00:41:17.832 --> 00:41:22.270
Relieve our collector
of his moral conflict.

663
00:41:27.642 --> 00:41:29.643
(gasping)

664
00:41:50.031 --> 00:41:52.232
(grunting)

665
00:41:56.369 --> 00:41:57.937
(sobbing)

666
00:42:00.173 --> 00:42:02.174
I beg of you. Please!

667
00:42:02.275 --> 00:42:04.009
Find the God you defend.

668
00:42:04.110 --> 00:42:05.377
Have mercy. please.

669
00:42:05.478 --> 00:42:07.379
Not for me.
but for the innocent heart

670
00:42:07.480 --> 00:42:09.748
beating inside. please.

671
00:42:09.849 --> 00:42:13.419
Please.

672
00:42:13.519 --> 00:42:15.754
Please.

673
00:42:15.855 --> 00:42:17.423
(praying quietly)

674
00:42:25.264 --> 00:42:27.265
(sobbing)

675
00:42:42.448 --> 00:42:44.716
Run.

676
00:42:44.817 --> 00:42:47.118
And don't ever come back here.
not anywhere in this shire.

677
00:42:47.219 --> 00:42:48.553
You'll be sure as dead.

678
00:42:48.654 --> 00:42:50.555
Go!

679
00:42:50.656 --> 00:42:52.591
(sobbing)

680
00:43:02.834 --> 00:43:04.835
♪

681
00:43:12.478 --> 00:43:15.079
(screaming)

682
00:43:18.517 --> 00:43:19.449
(screaming)

683
00:43:19.551 --> 00:43:21.719
(blade stabbing)

684
00:43:31.796 --> 00:43:33.797
(groans)

685
00:43:42.907 --> 00:43:44.774
(gasps)

686
00:43:52.282 --> 00:43:54.350
CORBETT:
The farmers will see the smoke.

687
00:43:54.451 --> 00:43:56.452
They won't ride
into a waiting attack.

688
00:43:56.554 --> 00:43:58.655
I want them alive.

689
00:43:58.756 --> 00:44:00.322
For now.

690
00:44:00.424 --> 00:44:02.791
Let them suffer this.

691
00:44:15.004 --> 00:44:17.005
(panting)

692
00:44:19.275 --> 00:44:20.675
(twig snaps)

693
00:44:23.112 --> 00:44:25.280
(sobbing)

694
00:44:25.381 --> 00:44:28.283
You... you.

695
00:44:28.384 --> 00:44:30.318
What are you...?

696
00:45:02.762 --> 00:45:05.533
_

697
00:45:09.977 --> 00:45:11.644
- (groans)
- Careful. boy.

698
00:45:11.745 --> 00:45:14.681
S-Sorry. Ma.
(groans)

699
00:45:20.087 --> 00:45:23.155
It's shit. Hmm?

700
00:45:23.257 --> 00:45:25.056
Like the lot of you.

701
00:45:25.157 --> 00:45:27.493
- Come here.
- I'm-I'm sorry.

702
00:45:27.594 --> 00:45:29.894
- (baby crying)
- Don't mother him.

703
00:45:29.995 --> 00:45:32.864
He needs to feel the pain
of his mistake.

704
00:45:32.964 --> 00:45:34.699
JESSAMY:
He feels it.

705
00:45:34.800 --> 00:45:37.535
I won't tend it.

706
00:45:37.636 --> 00:45:40.905
Please. enjoy the drink.

707
00:45:41.006 --> 00:45:42.774
We have another bird.

708
00:45:42.875 --> 00:45:44.609
I'll feed you
in short.

709
00:45:44.710 --> 00:45:46.977
- Don't put rule on me. whore!
- (groans)

710
00:45:48.780 --> 00:45:50.414
No.
(crying)

711
00:45:50.515 --> 00:45:51.715
Crawl. you cur!

712
00:45:51.816 --> 00:45:53.317
JESSAMY:
Please. Maddy.

713
00:45:53.418 --> 00:45:55.119
GAWAIN:
Show me the trench.

714
00:46:01.692 --> 00:46:03.093
The village!

715
00:46:03.194 --> 00:46:05.495
Hyah!
(shouts)

716
00:46:09.967 --> 00:46:11.334
(horse neighs)

717
00:46:19.843 --> 00:46:22.445
(Wilkin groans)

718
00:46:22.546 --> 00:46:25.148
(shuddering breaths)

719
00:46:25.249 --> 00:46:26.449
No.

720
00:46:26.550 --> 00:46:29.117
(panting)

721
00:46:29.218 --> 00:46:31.186
No.

722
00:46:31.287 --> 00:46:33.221
(crying)

723
00:46:38.527 --> 00:46:40.728
(crying)

724
00:47:00.449 --> 00:47:02.450
(panting)

725
00:47:10.592 --> 00:47:13.226
(crying softly)

726
00:47:13.327 --> 00:47:15.061
Dear child.

727
00:47:21.335 --> 00:47:22.769
(panting)

728
00:47:28.274 --> 00:47:30.275
Oh...

729
00:47:44.992 --> 00:47:46.959
(sobs)

730
00:47:47.060 --> 00:47:49.360
Sweet boy.

731
00:47:53.866 --> 00:47:56.200
My Rhys.

732
00:48:00.940 --> 00:48:03.341
This was Ventris.

733
00:48:03.442 --> 00:48:05.677
His collector as proof!

734
00:48:05.778 --> 00:48:08.179
Savage noble!

735
00:48:13.952 --> 00:48:16.521
Damn your holy destiny.

736
00:48:21.126 --> 00:48:23.928
(sobbing):
Devil Christ. Damn you.

737
00:48:46.084 --> 00:48:48.085
(grunting)

738
00:49:02.032 --> 00:49:04.033
(panting)

739
00:49:13.577 --> 00:49:15.578
(grunts)

740
00:49:18.815 --> 00:49:20.549
JACOB:
The sword.

741
00:49:22.719 --> 00:49:25.221
Crest of Edward the First.

742
00:49:29.691 --> 00:49:31.092
(grunts)

743
00:49:31.193 --> 00:49:33.161
CALO:
Where does he ride?

744
00:49:33.262 --> 00:49:35.230
To meet the devil.

745
00:49:35.331 --> 00:49:37.698
As are we.

746
00:49:37.799 --> 00:49:39.434
Our families...

747
00:49:39.535 --> 00:49:41.436
Will be avenged.

748
00:49:41.537 --> 00:49:43.338
- (horse neighs)
- Hup!

749
00:49:43.439 --> 00:49:45.373
(grunts)

750
00:49:56.584 --> 00:49:58.853
See to the dead.

751
00:49:58.954 --> 00:50:00.420
This is my fight.

752
00:50:00.522 --> 00:50:03.157
We've all earned this horror.

753
00:50:07.962 --> 00:50:11.498
I've no plan but vengeance.

754
00:50:11.599 --> 00:50:14.168
The only plan left.

755
00:50:25.713 --> 00:50:27.280
Yea. then.

756
00:50:27.381 --> 00:50:29.114
To Castle Ventris.

757
00:50:29.216 --> 00:50:30.716
- (horse neighs)
- Ha!

758
00:50:33.654 --> 00:50:35.655
(shouting)

759
00:50:57.610 --> 00:51:00.245
This is mine.

760
00:51:00.346 --> 00:51:02.280
(shuddering breaths)

761
00:51:04.884 --> 00:51:06.585
My due.

762
00:51:06.686 --> 00:51:09.722
My sorrow.

763
00:51:14.828 --> 00:51:17.038
Forgive me.

764
00:51:19.665 --> 00:51:21.666
(sizzling. quiet gasping)

765
00:51:26.071 --> 00:51:28.072
(panting. sobbing)

766
00:51:40.050 --> 00:51:42.485
The witch.

767
00:51:49.827 --> 00:51:51.794
What brings you so far east.

768
00:51:51.895 --> 00:51:53.629
woman?

769
00:51:53.731 --> 00:51:56.599
The same thing
that brings all of you.

770
00:51:56.700 --> 00:51:58.868
We flee the darkness.

771
00:51:58.969 --> 00:52:01.437
Did you witness the massacre?

772
00:52:01.538 --> 00:52:03.439
No.

773
00:52:03.540 --> 00:52:07.809
But I will witness yours
unless you alter your purpose.

774
00:52:07.910 --> 00:52:10.779
There's nothing to alter.

775
00:52:10.880 --> 00:52:12.513
We face what's ahead.

776
00:52:12.615 --> 00:52:17.452
But you do not need
to face it alone.

777
00:52:17.553 --> 00:52:22.057
Your cynic-- he has ties
to the way of victory.

778
00:52:32.167 --> 00:52:35.703
You are all knots and coil.

779
00:52:35.804 --> 00:52:37.204
(inhales)

780
00:52:37.306 --> 00:52:40.040
Pain of yesterday's
fierce effort.

781
00:52:40.142 --> 00:52:41.476
(sighs softly)

782
00:52:43.479 --> 00:52:45.880
So you found your bandits.

783
00:52:45.981 --> 00:52:47.848
No.

784
00:52:47.949 --> 00:52:50.785
But we met with the
proof of their guilt.

785
00:52:52.788 --> 00:52:54.755
And you've returned
with that proof?

786
00:52:54.856 --> 00:52:57.357
(chuckles)

787
00:52:57.458 --> 00:53:00.261
Difficult to carry
bone and slag.

788
00:53:00.361 --> 00:53:01.495
(door opens)

789
00:53:01.596 --> 00:53:03.597
CORBETT:
My lord.

790
00:53:03.698 --> 00:53:05.833
A scout came through from
midshire this morning.

791
00:53:05.934 --> 00:53:08.567
Spotted seven men
traveling east last night.

792
00:53:08.669 --> 00:53:11.404
One with a sword
bearing Longshanks' mark.

793
00:53:11.505 --> 00:53:13.406
Our bandits on a
mission. perhaps.

794
00:53:13.507 --> 00:53:15.842
Taking their vengeance
to my gate?

795
00:53:15.943 --> 00:53:18.278
Are they that mad with grief?

796
00:53:18.378 --> 00:53:21.781
Or soldiers willing to die
in service of their sorrow.

797
00:53:21.882 --> 00:53:23.950
I think it best
we meet them in journey.

798
00:53:24.051 --> 00:53:27.287
away from anyone who may see
this fool play as valiant.

799
00:53:27.387 --> 00:53:28.721
Stay.

800
00:53:28.823 --> 00:53:30.890
Protect the walls.

801
00:53:30.991 --> 00:53:32.624
Prepare a full legion
of foot soldiers.

802
00:53:32.725 --> 00:53:34.893
I'll gut this warrior bandit.

803
00:53:34.994 --> 00:53:37.595
Choke him cold with a snare
of his own entrails.

804
00:53:37.697 --> 00:53:39.631
A fine plan. my lord.

805
00:53:43.336 --> 00:53:45.737
Are you waiting
for a royal proclamation?

806
00:53:45.839 --> 00:53:47.405
Go with him. Reeve.

807
00:53:47.506 --> 00:53:49.674
Yes. indeed.
Chamberlain.

808
00:53:49.775 --> 00:53:51.109
My lady.

809
00:54:00.319 --> 00:54:02.320
(horses neighing)

810
00:54:15.501 --> 00:54:17.836
Who are you. traveler?

811
00:54:17.936 --> 00:54:19.837
Gawain Maddox. milord.

812
00:54:19.937 --> 00:54:21.572
I come up from the South.

813
00:54:21.673 --> 00:54:23.407
Punisher by trade.

814
00:54:23.508 --> 00:54:25.442
You have tools in possession?

815
00:54:25.543 --> 00:54:27.010
Yea'on.

816
00:54:27.111 --> 00:54:28.445
Ride with us.

817
00:54:28.546 --> 00:54:31.081
I may need
your services.

818
00:54:31.182 --> 00:54:33.350
My family.

819
00:54:33.451 --> 00:54:34.852
Ride the main trail north.

820
00:54:34.952 --> 00:54:36.787
It leads to Castle Ventris.

821
00:54:36.888 --> 00:54:38.822
They can wait there.

822
00:54:40.824 --> 00:54:42.792
Just follow on.

823
00:54:42.893 --> 00:54:44.827
I'll be with you.

824
00:54:51.301 --> 00:54:53.302
(horses sputtering)

825
00:55:06.349 --> 00:55:10.185
Do you remember me.
Earl Constable?

826
00:55:12.222 --> 00:55:14.223
I'm the knight
you sent to his death

827
00:55:14.324 --> 00:55:17.526
at the hands
of the hoarding Scots.

828
00:55:18.560 --> 00:55:20.461
Impossible.

829
00:55:20.562 --> 00:55:24.031
You know this man. my lord?

830
00:55:24.133 --> 00:55:27.401
If you are indeed
that knight.

831
00:55:27.503 --> 00:55:31.071
you're either a
deserter or a ghost.

832
00:55:31.173 --> 00:55:34.442
If not dead then.

833
00:55:34.543 --> 00:55:36.477
then dead now.

834
00:55:42.216 --> 00:55:46.153
I live with the terror
of your betrayal every day.

835
00:55:48.957 --> 00:55:52.893
But I'll spare you that pain.

836
00:55:52.994 --> 00:55:55.829
Death will quiet your mind.

837
00:56:04.938 --> 00:56:07.006
They're all rebels. milord.

838
00:56:09.377 --> 00:56:12.712
Time to go back to hell.
Marcher Baron!

839
00:56:13.614 --> 00:56:14.914
(whistles)

840
00:56:15.015 --> 00:56:16.182
(horses neighing)

841
00:56:19.353 --> 00:56:22.288
<i>Deus vult!</i>

842
00:56:22.389 --> 00:56:23.822
(men shouting)

843
00:56:47.279 --> 00:56:49.247
(yells)

844
00:57:18.642 --> 00:57:19.808
Go. go. go!

845
00:57:23.513 --> 00:57:25.013
(screams)

846
00:57:28.752 --> 00:57:30.620
(neighs)

847
00:57:49.538 --> 00:57:50.872
(grunts)

848
00:58:07.088 --> 00:58:08.355
(screams)

849
00:58:39.419 --> 00:58:43.355
Not ghost. nor deserter.

850
00:58:43.456 --> 00:58:46.224
Nor hood.

851
00:58:52.096 --> 00:58:53.764
(yells)

852
00:59:02.307 --> 00:59:03.874
(yells)

853
00:59:10.948 --> 00:59:11.981
(yells)

854
00:59:25.196 --> 00:59:26.895
VENTRIS:
London will hunt down

855
00:59:26.996 --> 00:59:30.433
the hooded bandits
and crush your toy rebellion.

856
00:59:30.534 --> 00:59:32.568
I've no rebellion.

857
00:59:32.669 --> 00:59:34.437
Just a need to see you die.

858
00:59:38.075 --> 00:59:39.108
(yells)

859
00:59:56.726 --> 00:59:58.727
♪

860
01:00:27.075 --> 01:00:29.677
How is he?
Will he heal?

861
01:00:29.778 --> 01:00:33.514
Only blood runs.
no other humors.

862
01:00:33.615 --> 01:00:35.549
He will sleep.

863
01:00:43.557 --> 01:00:45.692
BERBER:
Ventris was right.

864
01:00:45.793 --> 01:00:47.226
The king's army

865
01:00:47.328 --> 01:00:51.197
will come. hunt down
the hooded thieves.

866
01:00:51.299 --> 01:00:54.567
Yea. No rock unturned until our shit
holes are split on the cradle.

867
01:00:54.669 --> 01:00:55.602
Mm.

868
01:00:57.437 --> 01:00:59.871
Your. uh...

869
01:00:59.973 --> 01:01:02.908
your dark friend--
is he. um...

870
01:01:03.009 --> 01:01:04.610
in our pope's grace?

871
01:01:04.711 --> 01:01:07.579
A moor. converted
in his homeland.

872
01:01:09.749 --> 01:01:11.883
A good Catholic like us all.

873
01:01:13.119 --> 01:01:16.121
Yea. Bloody work
is the Lord's.

874
01:01:16.222 --> 01:01:17.455
TORAN:
Indeed.

875
01:01:20.359 --> 01:01:22.493
I need a name
to offer my thanks.

876
01:01:22.594 --> 01:01:24.161
Gruffudd.

877
01:01:24.262 --> 01:01:27.031
You're the one
they call "the wolf."

878
01:01:27.132 --> 01:01:28.999
I'm called many
hard things.

879
01:01:29.100 --> 01:01:30.435
Most by my wife.

880
01:01:30.536 --> 01:01:33.070
Thank you for answering
our plea. Gruffudd.

881
01:01:33.171 --> 01:01:34.739
We serve each
other. friend.

882
01:01:34.840 --> 01:01:37.207
The baron's forged weapons
will be a welcome change

883
01:01:37.309 --> 01:01:39.276
from our sticks
and cobbled blades.

884
01:01:39.377 --> 01:01:41.145
Ventris has lost
nearly two legions.

885
01:01:41.246 --> 01:01:42.480
His army is weakened.

886
01:01:42.581 --> 01:01:44.214
We're not ready to storm walls.

887
01:01:44.316 --> 01:01:45.817
Even with noble swords.

888
01:01:45.918 --> 01:01:49.753
But word of this victory
will spread and it will inspire.

889
01:01:49.854 --> 01:01:51.087
Our numbers
will grow.

890
01:01:51.188 --> 01:01:52.823
I have no doubt.

891
01:01:52.924 --> 01:01:56.092
Godspeed for your knight's
return to sound body.

892
01:01:56.193 --> 01:01:58.394
An unlikely ally
in our fight.

893
01:01:58.496 --> 01:02:00.396
Let him know there
may come a time

894
01:02:00.498 --> 01:02:02.198
when I collect
on this favor.

895
01:02:11.408 --> 01:02:13.509
Toran. Moor!

896
01:02:19.483 --> 01:02:21.050
You crazy witch!

897
01:02:27.757 --> 01:02:29.158
To what end

898
01:02:29.259 --> 01:02:31.194
does this devilry serve?

899
01:02:34.597 --> 01:02:36.598
(grunting)

900
01:02:45.441 --> 01:02:47.409
The baron has returned?

901
01:02:47.510 --> 01:02:50.412
No. But I have
news of his need.

902
01:02:50.513 --> 01:02:52.614
At Heaven's Eye.
we saw the rebel symbols.

903
01:02:52.715 --> 01:02:55.984
Lord Ventris sent me back
to secure more troops.

904
01:02:57.819 --> 01:03:00.287
Sent you back? Alone?

905
01:03:00.389 --> 01:03:02.056
Not to spare arms he may need.

906
01:03:02.157 --> 01:03:04.091
I welcomed the risk
of riding apart.

907
01:03:15.870 --> 01:03:18.406
Gather what men we can spare.

908
01:03:18.507 --> 01:03:20.174
With haste.

909
01:03:23.811 --> 01:03:25.679
Shall I find
the baroness?

910
01:03:25.780 --> 01:03:28.682
No. You should find a bath.

911
01:03:28.783 --> 01:03:31.351
You reek of shit.

912
01:03:31.452 --> 01:03:32.853
And fear.

913
01:03:49.736 --> 01:03:51.737
(sighs)

914
01:04:16.796 --> 01:04:18.797
(groans)

915
01:04:24.404 --> 01:04:27.205
You join the living.

916
01:04:27.306 --> 01:04:28.906
Who did this?

917
01:04:29.007 --> 01:04:31.109
The healer.

918
01:04:31.210 --> 01:04:33.144
She offered no reason.

919
01:04:40.619 --> 01:04:42.019
(groans)

920
01:05:03.374 --> 01:05:05.375
Cut her binds.

921
01:05:18.856 --> 01:05:21.323
Why did you cut and scar me?

922
01:05:21.424 --> 01:05:24.127
To save you.

923
01:05:24.227 --> 01:05:26.562
Your only chance

924
01:05:26.663 --> 01:05:29.365
to live is to be supposed dead.

925
01:05:31.701 --> 01:05:33.735
He gives you that gift.

926
01:05:52.155 --> 01:05:54.622
Who are you. woman?

927
01:05:54.724 --> 01:05:56.457
Truly.

928
01:05:56.559 --> 01:05:59.494
What's your
interest in me?

929
01:06:01.998 --> 01:06:05.500
You have a fate...

930
01:06:05.601 --> 01:06:07.535
that you must learn to hold.

931
01:06:07.636 --> 01:06:12.507
One that will forever
mark your place in time.

932
01:06:14.543 --> 01:06:17.212
I am here to help
tell that story.

933
01:06:19.248 --> 01:06:21.283
My story is over.

934
01:06:21.384 --> 01:06:23.184
No.

935
01:06:23.286 --> 01:06:26.621
It is just begun.

936
01:06:26.722 --> 01:06:29.756
The angel spoke the truth.

937
01:06:33.795 --> 01:06:35.996
The angel?

938
01:06:36.097 --> 01:06:39.233
The bright child
who came to you.

939
01:06:41.069 --> 01:06:42.736
How...

940
01:06:44.739 --> 01:06:48.775
I've never whispered
a word of that to anyone.

941
01:06:50.812 --> 01:06:53.580
I hear the same voices.

942
01:06:57.084 --> 01:07:00.954
It's time to lay down
this sword. Wilkin Brattle.

943
01:07:02.557 --> 01:07:04.691
(angel child's voice):
Your savior needs you

944
01:07:04.792 --> 01:07:07.961
to live the life
of a different man.

945
01:07:36.033 --> 01:07:38.033
Unhitch one of the
horses. brother.

946
01:07:38.134 --> 01:07:40.502
Then go join the
others at the caves.

947
01:07:40.603 --> 01:07:44.239
I think I'll finish
the ride. friend.

948
01:07:44.340 --> 01:07:46.942
A plan hatched by a witch--
what's to worry?

949
01:07:48.945 --> 01:07:53.548
We deliver the dead. tell
the tale. and ride off.

950
01:07:53.650 --> 01:07:56.217
Free men. no price
on our head.

951
01:07:56.318 --> 01:07:58.085
It's a sound devise.

952
01:07:58.187 --> 01:08:00.621
Simple enough an executioner
could carry it forth.

953
01:08:00.721 --> 01:08:02.623
(chuckles)

954
01:08:02.723 --> 01:08:04.791
And what say
of your purpose.

955
01:08:04.892 --> 01:08:08.462
What name for you?
Sneermonger?

956
01:08:10.532 --> 01:08:14.468
Well. my da. he wanted
to call me Marshal.

957
01:08:14.569 --> 01:08:17.171
But my ma thought it
too destined to war.

958
01:08:17.272 --> 01:08:20.073
Ma got the name.
da got the destiny.

959
01:08:20.175 --> 01:08:22.108
Yea. indeed.

960
01:08:22.209 --> 01:08:24.110
And what of your father?

961
01:08:24.211 --> 01:08:26.146
You never tell of anything.

962
01:08:28.849 --> 01:08:32.152
There's nothing to tell.
I don't have one.

963
01:08:34.955 --> 01:08:36.355
(grunts)

964
01:08:38.793 --> 01:08:41.527
(children's choir
singing Latin hymn)

965
01:08:53.940 --> 01:08:56.341
(choir continues
singing Latin hymn)

966
01:09:15.627 --> 01:09:17.294
(choir continues)

967
01:09:17.395 --> 01:09:18.796
ISABEL:
Pardon. Baroness.

968
01:09:18.897 --> 01:09:20.264
(choir stops singing)

969
01:09:20.365 --> 01:09:21.899
Outsiders have come.

970
01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:23.334
They bring sad news.

971
01:09:38.515 --> 01:09:40.516
Bring him down.

972
01:10:17.353 --> 01:10:20.489
My deepest condolences.
Lady Love.

973
01:10:20.590 --> 01:10:22.858
Let's bring you and the baron
into the castle

974
01:10:22.959 --> 01:10:24.893
so you can mourn in peace.

975
01:10:35.470 --> 01:10:38.807
Have the baron taken
to the sacrament room.

976
01:10:49.217 --> 01:10:51.551
Who are you?

977
01:10:54.555 --> 01:10:56.556
Gawain Maddox. milady.

978
01:10:56.657 --> 01:11:00.593
Punisher by trade.
from the southern land.

979
01:11:00.695 --> 01:11:02.595
This is Marshal.

980
01:11:02.697 --> 01:11:07.399
a journey soldier-- he aids me
in the capture of the accused.

981
01:11:07.500 --> 01:11:09.836
Tell me of his death.

982
01:11:09.937 --> 01:11:13.005
We met the baron
at Heaven's Eye.

983
01:11:13.106 --> 01:11:15.007
Called upon us
to ride with him.

984
01:11:15.108 --> 01:11:16.608
At the grass fields.

985
01:11:16.710 --> 01:11:18.845
they crossed a band
of hooded thieves.

986
01:11:18.946 --> 01:11:20.279
Took a fierce run.

987
01:11:20.380 --> 01:11:22.915
Noblemen cut down
the seven of them.

988
01:11:23.016 --> 01:11:25.083
WILKIN:
Before the baron could rally.

989
01:11:25.184 --> 01:11:26.985
rebels attacked.

990
01:11:27.086 --> 01:11:29.321
50 or more.

991
01:11:29.421 --> 01:11:32.958
Caught the ranks tired
and out of formation.

992
01:11:33.059 --> 01:11:36.995
Your husband fought gallantly.
but the numbers were too steep.

993
01:11:38.397 --> 01:11:40.031
I'm sorry.

994
01:11:44.169 --> 01:11:46.003
Old men and boys.

995
01:11:46.104 --> 01:11:48.372
WILKIN: Your mail-clad soldiers
were too heavy to carry.

996
01:11:50.441 --> 01:11:53.143
We can send troops there
to collect the others.

997
01:11:53.245 --> 01:11:56.146
LADY LOVE: And what brings
an executioner to Ventrishire?

998
01:11:56.248 --> 01:11:58.048
Work. milady.

999
01:11:58.149 --> 01:12:00.084
I travel. go where
my services are needed.

1000
01:12:00.185 --> 01:12:02.119
RANDULF:
He lies!

1001
01:12:04.221 --> 01:12:05.989
This man is
not the executioner.

1002
01:12:08.092 --> 01:12:09.926
He's one of the thieves.

1003
01:12:10.027 --> 01:12:11.460
As is that one.

1004
01:12:11.561 --> 01:12:14.397
You're the liar. sir.

1005
01:12:14.498 --> 01:12:17.633
I've traveled with Gawain
for many years.

1006
01:12:17.734 --> 01:12:20.203
Dispatch a messenger
to Glamorgan for proof.

1007
01:12:20.304 --> 01:12:23.105
There is no other face
looks like this one.

1008
01:12:23.206 --> 01:12:25.307
WILKIN:
We just came

1009
01:12:25.408 --> 01:12:27.276
to deliver the dead.

1010
01:12:27.377 --> 01:12:29.311
Out of respect.

1011
01:12:29.412 --> 01:12:31.280
We'll leave if it upsets
your court.

1012
01:12:31.381 --> 01:12:34.783
You'll stay and be quartered.

1013
01:12:34.884 --> 01:12:38.120
The remedy for this dispute
is already here.

1014
01:12:39.622 --> 01:12:41.756
The wife and children
of Maddox. sent here

1015
01:12:41.857 --> 01:12:43.991
to wait for his return.

1016
01:12:47.563 --> 01:12:49.898
Come forward.

1017
01:12:52.802 --> 01:12:55.202
Tell us the truth.

1018
01:12:55.304 --> 01:12:57.639
Is this man indeed your husband?

1019
01:13:17.358 --> 01:13:19.359
(fussing)

1020
01:13:25.231 --> 01:13:27.032
(trembling breaths)

1021
01:13:27.133 --> 01:13:29.068
(whispers):
I'm sorry.

1022
01:13:35.776 --> 01:13:37.777
My love.

1023
01:13:40.313 --> 01:13:43.482
Good Maddy. thank God
you've come back safe.

1024
01:13:48.254 --> 01:13:50.055
This is lunacy!

1025
01:13:50.156 --> 01:13:52.624
She conspires with him!

1026
01:13:56.863 --> 01:13:59.730
Such tragedy...

1027
01:13:59.831 --> 01:14:02.200
lands on my name this day.

1028
01:14:08.040 --> 01:14:09.573
My dearest friend.

1029
01:14:09.674 --> 01:14:13.011
a life snuffed...

1030
01:14:13.112 --> 01:14:15.546
not in a fitting battle...

1031
01:14:16.815 --> 01:14:20.017
but by the ambush
of painted dogs.

1032
01:14:22.520 --> 01:14:25.889
And my kin.

1033
01:14:25.990 --> 01:14:28.791
Caught between two tales.

1034
01:14:28.893 --> 01:14:30.693
I speak only truth.
dear brother.

1035
01:14:30.794 --> 01:14:33.363
I have nothing to gain
from such a lie.

1036
01:14:33.464 --> 01:14:35.565
These men are
the bandits we pursued.

1037
01:14:35.666 --> 01:14:37.567
Did battle in the
fields beyond the eye.

1038
01:14:37.668 --> 01:14:40.570
I myself
and other honored knights

1039
01:14:40.671 --> 01:14:42.672
heard you tell
how you were dispatched

1040
01:14:42.773 --> 01:14:45.241
<i>before</i> any such fray.

1041
01:14:49.046 --> 01:14:50.513
Yea.

1042
01:14:50.614 --> 01:14:52.882
- I did. but...
WILKIN: - You may have

1043
01:14:52.983 --> 01:14:56.501
nothing to gain. but
you've much to hide.

1044
01:14:56.586 --> 01:15:00.156
We saw this man at the fray.

1045
01:15:00.257 --> 01:15:03.159
He tucked tail and slithered
away. letting his brothers

1046
01:15:03.260 --> 01:15:05.447
fall to the curs.

1047
01:15:05.996 --> 01:15:08.131
That's why he lies.

1048
01:15:08.232 --> 01:15:09.633
'Cause we know
the truth.

1049
01:15:09.734 --> 01:15:11.067
That's...

1050
01:15:11.168 --> 01:15:13.102
- I tell you. these are the...
CORBETT: - Enough!

1051
01:15:24.648 --> 01:15:27.316
So. then. Reeve...

1052
01:15:27.417 --> 01:15:30.619
you are either a false accuser

1053
01:15:30.720 --> 01:15:33.021
or you deserted your commander
in battle!

1054
01:15:35.023 --> 01:15:37.892
Both come with
a punishment of death!

1055
01:15:40.028 --> 01:15:42.497
(whispering):
Please...

1056
01:15:42.598 --> 01:15:44.399
Milus...

1057
01:15:44.500 --> 01:15:45.966
brother...

1058
01:15:46.067 --> 01:15:47.502
do not do this.

1059
01:15:48.103 --> 01:15:49.569
Take him!

1060
01:15:49.671 --> 01:15:51.238
Brother. we are blood.

1061
01:15:51.339 --> 01:15:52.972
Do not betray me.
Damn you!

1062
01:15:53.073 --> 01:15:54.473
Damn your half-hatred!

1063
01:15:54.574 --> 01:15:55.641
Damn y...

1064
01:15:55.742 --> 01:15:56.475
(grunts)

1065
01:15:56.576 --> 01:15:58.511
(gasping)

1066
01:15:58.612 --> 01:16:00.280
(Randulf yells)

1067
01:16:00.380 --> 01:16:03.016
I'm gonna speak
to the King!

1068
01:16:03.117 --> 01:16:04.383
Curse you!

1069
01:16:04.484 --> 01:16:05.919
I'll curse you
from hell!

1070
01:16:06.020 --> 01:16:07.787
(Randulf sobbing)

1071
01:16:15.895 --> 01:16:19.298
My shame is only
outdone by my sadness.

1072
01:16:21.334 --> 01:16:24.602
My deepest sympathies. Baroness.

1073
01:16:24.704 --> 01:16:28.073
I am in your service.
whatever the need.

1074
01:16:29.675 --> 01:16:31.809
Thank you. Milus.

1075
01:16:33.879 --> 01:16:36.780
I will do haste
with manor law and trial.

1076
01:16:38.884 --> 01:16:40.584
It is fitting...

1077
01:16:40.685 --> 01:16:42.686
that the man falsely accused

1078
01:16:42.787 --> 01:16:46.324
be the one who is skilled
to take his head.

1079
01:16:57.735 --> 01:17:01.171
Welcome to Castle Ventris.
executioner.

1080
01:17:32.468 --> 01:17:34.702
Baroness.

1081
01:17:34.803 --> 01:17:37.538
The priest. he said I could
come for evening prayer.

1082
01:17:37.639 --> 01:17:39.140
Please. sit.

1083
01:17:39.241 --> 01:17:41.209
I welcome the chapel's use.

1084
01:17:41.310 --> 01:17:44.112
Few spend time here but me.

1085
01:17:47.850 --> 01:17:49.851
Do you mind?

1086
01:17:51.753 --> 01:17:53.387
Please.

1087
01:18:02.430 --> 01:18:04.431
I wouldn't think

1088
01:18:04.533 --> 01:18:07.969
one of your trade would
complicate things with prayer.

1089
01:18:10.506 --> 01:18:13.808
Perhaps it takes you
in deeper.

1090
01:18:18.747 --> 01:18:21.648
May I ask how
this happened?

1091
01:18:23.818 --> 01:18:26.119
It was given to me
by a healer.

1092
01:18:26.220 --> 01:18:29.288
A holy woman.

1093
01:18:29.390 --> 01:18:31.691
A reminder
of my need for faith.

1094
01:18:34.194 --> 01:18:36.295
Your soldier gave
the impression

1095
01:18:36.397 --> 01:18:38.231
it distinguished
you for some time.

1096
01:18:38.332 --> 01:18:41.801
Yet. the burn looks fresh.

1097
01:18:41.903 --> 01:18:44.571
I renew the vow
when my faith wavers.

1098
01:18:48.575 --> 01:18:50.976
You're bleeding.

1099
01:18:51.078 --> 01:18:53.379
Yea.

1100
01:18:53.480 --> 01:18:56.815
An angry branch
on last night's ride.

1101
01:18:56.917 --> 01:18:59.285
May I?

1102
01:18:59.386 --> 01:19:01.687
WILKIN:
In here. milady?

1103
01:19:01.788 --> 01:19:03.322
LADY LOVE:
No better one

1104
01:19:03.424 --> 01:19:05.724
to heal you than Him.

1105
01:19:16.602 --> 01:19:18.970
The physicker
should look at this.

1106
01:19:21.907 --> 01:19:26.311
(baby crying)

1107
01:19:38.624 --> 01:19:41.025
I'll find the physicker.

1108
01:19:41.126 --> 01:19:44.428
No. Stay.

1109
01:19:44.529 --> 01:19:46.230
Finish your devotion.

1110
01:19:46.331 --> 01:19:49.333
I'll have him find you.

1111
01:20:15.693 --> 01:20:19.362
Baroness?

1112
01:20:19.463 --> 01:20:22.565
I sent an emissary
to London

1113
01:20:22.667 --> 01:20:27.537
and one to Erik's brother
in Coventry.

1114
01:20:27.639 --> 01:20:32.574
I'm sure our king will offer
comfort and guidance

1115
01:20:32.676 --> 01:20:35.177
of how we proceed
to govern.

1116
01:20:35.278 --> 01:20:38.347
We proceed by
burying my husband.

1117
01:20:39.582 --> 01:20:41.884
Yes.

1118
01:20:41.985 --> 01:20:44.086
Of course.

1119
01:20:46.256 --> 01:20:48.658
Another thought.

1120
01:20:48.759 --> 01:20:50.692
my lady.

1121
01:20:50.793 --> 01:20:54.062
This executioner--

1122
01:20:54.164 --> 01:20:56.031
his arrival.

1123
01:20:56.132 --> 01:20:59.568
although it brought sadness--

1124
01:20:59.669 --> 01:21:01.870
it could turn
to good fortune.

1125
01:21:01.971 --> 01:21:03.305
How so?

1126
01:21:03.406 --> 01:21:05.874
If we secure him
and his soldier.

1127
01:21:05.975 --> 01:21:08.877
we gain skilled men
to hunt offenders

1128
01:21:08.978 --> 01:21:11.213
and carry out the correction.

1129
01:21:11.314 --> 01:21:15.750
Sends a sound message.

1130
01:21:15.851 --> 01:21:19.154
Ventrishire will not
suffer lawlessness.

1131
01:21:22.024 --> 01:21:25.493
That's well advised.
dear Chamberlain.

1132
01:21:25.594 --> 01:21:28.462
Good. I'll draft the letters

1133
01:21:28.564 --> 01:21:30.865
that bind them.

1134
01:21:50.018 --> 01:21:53.987
I have news. Maddox.

1135
01:21:55.590 --> 01:21:59.693
The trial was swift.
the guilt clear.

1136
01:22:01.262 --> 01:22:03.697
We will stage the execution
in the village square

1137
01:22:03.798 --> 01:22:06.100
midday tomorrow.

1138
01:22:12.273 --> 01:22:14.941
He's your blood.

1139
01:22:15.042 --> 01:22:17.377
There must be some...

1140
01:22:17.478 --> 01:22:20.747
due leniency. a brother's mercy?

1141
01:22:20.848 --> 01:22:23.116
You rid me of a mistake

1142
01:22:23.217 --> 01:22:27.621
influenced by familial guilt.

1143
01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:33.059
No kin. no worries.

1144
01:22:34.928 --> 01:22:37.663
But of course.
you wouldn't understand that.

1145
01:22:37.764 --> 01:22:41.333
Being a family man.

1146
01:22:41.434 --> 01:22:44.436
And you're the final word
of justice here?

1147
01:22:46.639 --> 01:22:49.942
As well as chancellor
and advisor.

1148
01:22:50.043 --> 01:22:53.679
You'll find that nothing passes

1149
01:22:53.780 --> 01:22:57.116
through this shire
without me touching it.

1150
01:22:57.217 --> 01:22:59.551
I'm afraid that's a lesson
I'll have to miss.

1151
01:22:59.652 --> 01:23:01.553
I move on after tomorrow.

1152
01:23:01.654 --> 01:23:03.722
Ah. but that's my news.

1153
01:23:03.823 --> 01:23:07.993
You and your soldier
will stay on.

1154
01:23:08.094 --> 01:23:10.562
Your position is now standing.

1155
01:23:15.134 --> 01:23:17.536
We're journeyman.

1156
01:23:17.637 --> 01:23:19.404
Travelers.

1157
01:23:19.506 --> 01:23:21.205
Now. you have a home.

1158
01:23:21.306 --> 01:23:25.242
I'm sure that will be
a comfort to your

1159
01:23:25.343 --> 01:23:28.312
wife and wee things.

1160
01:23:32.117 --> 01:23:34.552
(breathing loudly)

1161
01:23:42.193 --> 01:23:44.628
Why are you doing this?

1162
01:23:47.297 --> 01:23:50.133
Our buried truths bind us.

1163
01:23:50.234 --> 01:23:53.136
And your skills
will serve me.

1164
01:23:59.343 --> 01:24:01.745
I need a man

1165
01:24:01.846 --> 01:24:04.147
with the heart
of a dragon.

1166
01:24:28.605 --> 01:24:31.006
(scratching)

1167
01:24:33.242 --> 01:24:35.677
(soft gasp)

1168
01:24:37.947 --> 01:24:40.382
ANNORA:
Ludwig?

1169
01:24:52.061 --> 01:24:54.463
(shallow breathing)

1170
01:25:07.943 --> 01:25:11.646
We need to ready our faith.

1171
01:25:11.747 --> 01:25:16.517
(shakily):
<i>Ja. meine Liebe.</i>

1172
01:25:22.625 --> 01:25:24.993
(breathing shakily)

1173
01:25:42.132 --> 01:25:44.567
<i>Ego auctoritate</i>

1174
01:25:44.668 --> 01:25:47.737
<i>ipsius te absolvo</i>

1175
01:25:47.838 --> 01:25:52.107
<i>ab omni vinculo excommunicationis
et interdicti...</i>

1176
01:25:52.208 --> 01:25:55.177
- (boys singing chant in Latin)
<i>- ...in quantum possum</i>

1177
01:25:55.277 --> 01:25:58.113
<i>- et tu indiges.</i>
<i>- (groaning)</i>

1178
01:25:58.214 --> 01:26:01.349
<i>Ego te absolvo</i>

1179
01:26:01.450 --> 01:26:04.419
<i>a peccatis tuis</i>

1180
01:26:04.520 --> 01:26:07.222
<i>in nomine Patris.</i>
<i>et Filii.</i>

1181
01:26:07.323 --> 01:26:08.989
<i>et Spiritus Sancti. Amen.</i>

1182
01:26:13.595 --> 01:26:16.630
(Randulf groaning)

1183
01:26:23.105 --> 01:26:25.505
(singing chant continues)

1184
01:26:31.311 --> 01:26:33.679
Blades have been grinded. sir.

1185
01:26:43.022 --> 01:26:45.357
(groans softly)

1186
01:27:03.475 --> 01:27:05.910
(groans softly)

1187
01:27:12.417 --> 01:27:14.785
(singing chant continues)

1188
01:27:19.490 --> 01:27:22.292
(whispering. laughing)

1189
01:27:22.393 --> 01:27:24.728
(inhales deeply)

1190
01:27:24.829 --> 01:27:26.730
(exhales deeply)

1191
01:27:26.831 --> 01:27:29.165
(quietly):
Help me.

1192
01:27:32.469 --> 01:27:34.971
(crowd murmuring)

1193
01:28:16.245 --> 01:28:19.881
Always.

1194
01:28:34.396 --> 01:28:35.829
You'll need this. headsman.

1195
01:28:35.930 --> 01:28:38.699
Little Rand
was full of shit.

1196
01:28:38.800 --> 01:28:40.601
(laughter)

1197
01:28:40.702 --> 01:28:42.870
A stuffed clown.

1198
01:28:42.970 --> 01:28:44.033
(laughter)

1199
01:28:44.206 --> 01:28:45.607
You best take another.

1200
01:28:45.708 --> 01:28:47.475
Yeah. His ass will spout
like a fountain.

1201
01:28:47.576 --> 01:28:50.144
(laughter)

1202
01:28:50.245 --> 01:28:51.679
Who did you spring from?

1203
01:28:51.780 --> 01:28:53.848
(laughter)

1204
01:29:18.406 --> 01:29:20.374
(yelling)

1205
01:29:21.409 --> 01:29:23.210
(thudding)

1205
01:29:24.305 --> 01:30:24.470
Do you want subtitles for any video?
